<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/style.css">
  </head>
  <body>
      <header style="background-image: url('<%= image %>')">
          <h1><%= title %></h1>
      </header>
      <section>
          <div id="forms">
              <h2>Welcome to <%= title %></h2>
              <p>Max Kompressor is your friend in kompressing jpeg images to the max. Using libgd this node.js application kompresses your <code>image/jpeg</code> to level <code>0</code>, i.e. zero, nil, naught.</p>
              <form method="post" action="/" enctype="multipart/form-data">
                  <fieldset>
                      <legend>Upload form</legend>
                      File upload: <input type="file" name="image" accept="image/jpeg"><br>
                      <input type="submit" value="Submit upload">
                  </fieldset>
              </form>
              <form method="post" action="/" enctype="multipart/form-data">
                  <fieldset>
                      <legend>URL form</legend>
                      URL: <input type="text" name="url" autofocus="autofocus" style="width: 300px;" placeholder="paste URL here..."><br>
                      <input type="submit" value="Submit URL">
                  </fieldset>
              </form>
          </div>
          <div class="result">
              <img src="<%= image %>" alt="">
          </div>
      </section>
      <aside>
          <div id="note">
              <h3>Max kompresses art</h3>
              <p>Max' help is used by <a href="http://www.y-a-v-a.org" target="_blank">y-a-v-a.org</a> as a means to reinterpret the history of painting: how much of the aura of a depiction of a painting is left after a mathematical interference that lossyly kompresses these images to its technical maximum? Decide for yourself...</p>
          </div>
          <div id="gallery">
              <script src="http://y-a-v-a.tumblr.com/js"></script>
          </div>
      </aside>
      <footer>
          <p>Done by <a href="http://www.y-a-v-a.org" target="_blank">y-a-v-a.org</a> in html5, css3, javascript and node.js</p>
          <p>view results @ <a href="http://y-a-v-a.tumblr.com/" target="_blank">http://y-a-v-a.tumblr.com/</a></p>
      </footer>
  </body>

